    "plan_content": "Here is a detailed summary of the plan:\n\n---\n\n## Plan: Add `Bun.INI` to Bun\n\n### What was discovered\n\nThe existing `src/ini.zig` is **intentionally off-limits** — it's a npm-config parser tightly coupled to `DotEnv.Loader`, env var expansion, and `.npmrc`-specific features. The task requires a **new, self-contained** parser in `src/interchange/ini.zig`.\n\nAll other format namespaces (TOML, YAML, JSONC, JSON5) follow an identical 4-layer pattern that `Bun.INI` will mirror exactly.\n\n---\n\n### Files to create (3)\n\n1. **`src/interchange/ini.zig`** — Pure Zig INI parser with a `parse(source, log, allocator) !Expr` function. Handles: `[section]` → nested objects, `key = value` pairs, `;`/`#` comment lines, value coercions (true/false/null/numbers), `key[]` array syntax, inline comment stripping. No DotEnv dependency.\n\n2. **`src/bun.js/api/INIObject.zig`** — JS bridge mirroring `TOMLObject.zig`:\n   - `parse`: uses the AST → `js_printer.printJSON` → `toJSByParseJSON` pipeline (identical to TOML)\n   - `stringify`: walks JS object properties and emits INI text (scalars first, then `[section]` blocks for nested objects)\n\n3. **`test/js/bun/ini/ini.test.ts`** — Tests covering parse (key=value, sections, comments, coercions, errors, empty input) and stringify (simple objects, sections, round-trip).\n\n### Files to modify (5)\n\n4. **`src/bun.js/api.zig`** — `pub const INIObject = @import(\"./api/INIObject.zig\");`\n\n5. **`src/bun.js/api/BunObject.zig`** — 4 locations:\n   - Add `pub const INI = toJSLazyPropertyCallback(Bun.getINIObject);` (line ~70)\n   - Add `@export(&BunObject.INI, ...)` in `exportAll()` (line ~140)\n   - Add `pub fn getINIObject(...)` getter (after `getYAMLObject`, line ~1289)\n   - Add `const INIObject = bun.api.INIObject;` (bottom imports, line ~2083)\n\n6. **`src/bun.js/bindings/BunObject.cpp`** — Add one row to `@begin bunObjectTable`: `INI  BunObject_lazyPropCb_wrap_INI  DontDelete|PropertyCallback`\n\n7. **`src/bun.js/bindings/BunObject+exports.h`** — Add `macro(INI) \\` to `FOR_EACH_GETTER`\n\n8. **`packages/bun-types/bun.d.ts`** — Add `namespace INI { parse(input: string): object; stringify(value: object): string; }`",
